Name: chemicals undefined use
Definition: Chemicals undefined use.

Name: unidentified generally dark-coloured oil-like chemicals
Definition: Unidentified generally dark-coloured oil-like chemicals, i.e. no chemical analysis carried out.

Name: grease
Definition: Lubricating grease (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis).

Name: other generally dark-coloured oil-like chemicals
Definition: Other generally dark-coloured oil-like chemicals includes e.g. Tall oil, also called "liquid rosin" (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis).

Name: plastic 4/6-pack yokes & six-pack rings
Definition: Four or six pack rings or yokes are a set of connected plastic rings that are used in multi-packs of drinks, particularly of drinks cans, to hold the cans together.

Name: oil
Definition: All types of oil usually found as viscous droplets or mats e.g., on a beach (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis). This is usually the sludge that remains after centrifuging heavy fuel oil before use as fuel by ships. It can also be crude oil, from loss of cargo, as well as hydraulic oil.

Name: tar
Definition: Tar is the name for any oil that has been in the marine environment for such a length of time that the more volatile components have evaporated - usually more dry than oil, but there is a smooth transition between oil and tar (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis).

Name: unidentified generally light-coloured paraffin-like chemicals
Definition: Unidentified generally light-coloured paraffin-like chemicals, i.e. no chemical analysis carried out.

Name: other generally light-coloured paraffin-like chemicals (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis)
Definition: Other generally light-coloured paraffin-like chemicals e.g. ethylene-oligomeres.

Name: plastic bags
Definition: Plastic bags

Name: vegetable oil
Definition: Vegetable oil, such as palm oil (only to be included after proof through chemical analysis).

Name: unidentified chemicals
Definition: Any unidentified chemicals i.e. no chemical analysis carried out.

Name: plastic shopping/carrier/grocery bags
Definition: Shopping bags are medium-sized bags, typically around 10–20 litres in volume (though much larger versions exist, especially for non-grocery shopping), that are used by shoppers to carry home their purchases. Shopping bags can be made with a variety of plastics.

Name: small plastic bags
Definition: Small plastic bags refer to small-sized bags such as freezer bags, zip-lock re-sealable food bags, poly bags, etc.

Name: the part that remains from tear-off plastic bags
Definition: Plastic packing bags are commonly found on the market in packs of 10, 20, 50, etc. This litter item refers to the part that remains after tearing-off the bags.

Name: cloth textile undefined use
Definition: Cloth textile undefined use.

Name: plastic bottles & containers other than food or personal hygiene and care related
Definition: Plastic bottles & containers other than food or personal hygiene and care related.

Name: plastic drink bottles ≤ 0.5 l
Definition: Plastic bottles and containers with a volume of 0.5 litres or less, used to hold water, juice or other drinks for consumption.

Name: plastic drink bottles >0.5 l
Definition: Plastic bottles and containers with a volume larger than 0.5 litres, used to hold water, juice or other drinks for consumption.

Name: plastic bottles and containers of cleaning products
Definition: Bottles and containers of cleaning products such as detergents, toilet cleaners, glass cleaners, etc.

Name: recreation related cloth and textile items
Definition: Recreation related cloth and textile items.

Name: plastic food bottles & containers
Definition: Plastic food bottles & containers.

Name: plastic beach use related body care and cosmetic bottles and containers
Definition: Bottles and containers of body care and cosmetics products used at the beach such as sunscreen, suntan or after sun lotion, etc.

Name: glass ceramic construction related waste
Definition: Glass ceramic construction related.

Name: plastic non-beach use related body care and cosmetic bottles and containers
Definition: Bottles and containers of body care and cosmetics products such as shampoo, shower gel, toothpaste, perfume and others that are not explicitly used at the beach.

Name: food consumption related glass and ceramic items
Definition: Food consumption related glass and ceramic items.

Name: other plastic bottles & containers (drums)
Definition: Other plastic bottles and containers such as drums (cylindrical containers) generally used for the transportation and storage of liquids and powders.

Name: glass and ceramic fisheries related items
Definition: Glass and ceramic fisheries related items.

Name: glass and ceramic lobster/crab/octopus pots and traps
Definition: Glass and ceramic lobster/crab/octopus pots and traps.

Name: plastic engine oil bottles & containers 2.5 cm  ≥ ≤  50 cm
Definition: Plastic bottles and containers smaller than 50 cm in any dimension, used for packaging motor oil, engine oil, or engine lubricant.

Name: glass ceramic undefined use
Definition: Glass ceramic undefined use.

Name: glass ceramic bottles & containers
Definition: Glass ceramic bottles & containers.

Name: plastic engine oil bottles & containers >50cm
Definition: Plastic bottles and containers bigger than 50 cm in any dimension, used for packaging motor oil, engine oil, or engine lubricant.

Name: plastic jerry cans
Definition: Large plastic flat-sided containers with a handle used for storing or transporting liquids, typically petrol or water.

Name: plastic injection gun containers/cartridges
Definition: A cartridge made of plastic for devices that are used to inject grease, silicone, or other fluids.

Name: glass light bulbs and fluorescent light tubes
Definition: Glass light bulbs and fluorescent light tubes.

Name: plastic crates, boxes, baskets
Definition: Plastic containers typically used to transport or store different types of items and products, other than fisheries and aquaculture related.

Name: plastic vehicle parts
Definition: Any part of a car or other transport vehicle made of artificial polymer materials and fibre glass. This can also include pieces of boats.

Name: other glass or ceramic items
Definition: Other identifiable ceramic items, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: other ceramic items
Definition: Other identifiable ceramic items, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: plastic caps and lids
Definition: Plastic caps and lids.

Name: metal construction related waste
Definition: Metal construction related waste.

Name: plastic caps/lids drinks
Definition: Plastic caps and lids from bottles and containers, used to hold water, juice or other drinks for consumption

Name: metal food consumption related
Definition: Metal food consumption related.

Name: metal food containers
Definition: Metal food containers.

Name: metal cans for food and drink
Definition: Metal cans for food and drink.

Name: plastic caps/lids chemicals, detergents (non-food)
Definition: Plastic caps and lids from bottles and containers of cleaning products (i.e. detergents, toilet cleaners, glass cleaners, etc.) and chemicals.

Name: plastic caps/lids unidentified
Definition: Plastic caps and lids from unidentified bottles and containers.

Name: plastic rings from bottle caps/lids
Definition: Plastic structures around the circumference (usually) of the closure that is often found attached below a closure in bottles, jars, and tubs. The bottom part of a cap that breaks off when the cap is screwed off.

Name: metal fisheries related
Definition: Metal fisheries related.

Name: plastic tobacco pouches / plastic cigarette packet packaging
Definition: Plastic containers (pouches, boxes) used for cigarettes and tobacco.

Name: plastic cigarette lighters
Definition: Small objects that produce a flame, commonly used for lighting cigarettes or cigars.

Name: metal undefined use
Definition: Metal undefined use.

Name: tobacco products with filters (cigarette butts with filters)
Definition: A cigarette filter, also known as a filter tip, is a component of a cigarette, placed at the one tip of the cigarette in order to absorb vapours and accumulate particulate smoke components. The filter is commonly made from synthetic plastic cellulose.

Name: metal bottles & containers
Definition: Metal bottles & containers.

Name: plastic pens and pen lids
Definition: Any writing or drawing utensils made predominately from artificial polymer materials.

Name: metal cans other than for food and drink
Definition: Metal cans.

Name: plastic combs/hair brushes/sunglasses
Definition: Plastic items used for untangling or arranging the hair, as well as plastic glasses tinted to protect the eyes from sunlight or glare.

Name: plastic crisps packets/sweets wrappers
Definition: Plastic food packets and wrappers created and designed in various colours, materials, shapes, sizes and styles for crisp food products (i.e., potato chips, etc.) or sweets (i.e., chocolates, candy, ice-creams, etc.).

Name: plastic lolly & ice-cream sticks
Definition: A plastic stick attached to the bottom of a popsicle/lolly/ice-cream or lollypop used as a handle to facilitate the eating process.

Name: plastic toys and party poppers
Definition: Any plastic object that children play with, as well as objects commonly used at parties. Party poppers are small devices used as an amusement at parties, which explode when a string is pulled, ejecting thin paper streamers.

Name: plastic cups and cup lids
Definition: Plastic cups and cup lids of foamed or non-foamed artificial polymer materials.

Name: plastic cutlery, plates and trays
Definition: Plastic cutlery, plates and trays.

Name: plastic straws and stirrers
Definition: Straws and stirrers for drinks.

Name: other plastic heavy-duty sacks
Definition: Non-salt heavy duty plastic sacks for content such as animal feed, fertilizers, garden rubbish, etc.

Name: plastic mesh bags
Definition: Plastic mesh bags.

Name: plastic cover packaging
Definition: Plastic cover packaging.

Name: plastic gloves
Definition: Plastic gloves.

Name: metal recreation related items
Definition: Metal recreation related items.

Name: plastic gloves (household/dishwashing, gardening)
Definition: Gloves used to do household chores such as dishwashing gardening, etc. They are typically made of different polymers including latex, nitrile rubber, polyvinyl chloride. Less heavy-duty than industrial gloves.

Name: metal vehicle related items
Definition: Metal vehicle related items.

Name: plastic gloves (industrial/professional applications)
Definition: Gloves specifically dedicated to industrial applications, mechanical, engineering, agriculture, fisheries and aquaculture and construction. They are typically made of different polymers including latex, nitrile rubber, polyvinyl chloride and neoprene.

Name: plastic crab/lobster traps (pots) and tops
Definition: Stationary plastic traps or pots used to catch crustaceans such as lobsters and crabs. Though the size and shape of the traps may vary, most feature a net covering and a cone-shaped entrance tunnel through which a crab or lobster is enticed with bait but cannot escape from.

Name: plastic waste from agriculture
Definition: Plastic waste from agriculture and horticulture.

Name: plastic sheeting from greenhouses
Definition: Plastic sheeting used to cover greenhouses generated during the construction, renovation, and demolition. This category is possibly only separable from other plastic sheeting by experienced workers.

Name: plastic irrigation pipes
Definition: Plastic irrigation pipes from agriculture generated during construction, renovation, and demolition.

Name: other plastic items from agriculture
Definition: Other plastic items from agriculture generated during construction, renovation, and demolition.

Name: plastic tags (fishing and industry)
Definition: Plastic tags used to mark fish and shellfish such as lobsters and plastic cargo seals (pull-tight) both usually with a serial number.

Name: trays for seedlings of foamed plastic
Definition: A foamed plastic tray in which seedlings are grown.

Name: plastic from aquaculture
Definition: Plastic from aquaculture.

Name: plastic equipment for holding or protecting shellfish
Definition: Plastic equipment for holding or protecting shellfish.

Name: plastic octopus pots
Definition: Pots made of plastic or PVC tubing, weighted with concrete, and typically having a volume of 4 litres. Octopus seeking refuge in the pots can be trapped.

Name: plastic mussels/oyster mesh bags, net sack, socks
Definition: A special bag or sack made of extruded net which is used for growing (underwater) oysters and other shellfish species. These bags can have different sizes and shapes e.g., sack-like and tubular and the mesh net can have different sizes.

Name: plastic oyster trays
Definition: A special tray made of square mesh used for growing oysters. Trays may be single, double or triple stacked, with or without feet, doors, v-braces and hooks.

Name: plastic sheeting from mussel culture (Tahitians)
Definition: Pieces of plastic sheeting about 50X40 cm which are cut at one end into fringes or stripes so they look a little like a grass skirt from Hawaii. They are used to protect mussel cultures from animals that feed on mussels.

Name: plastic rope (diameter more than 1cm)
Definition: A stout cord of strands of plastic fibres twisted or braided together, with a diameter larger than 1 cm.

Name: plastic string and cord (diameter less than 1cm)
Definition: String and cord (diameter less than 1cm).

Name: plastic nets and pieces of net including dolly ropes
Definition: Plastic nets and pieces of net including dolly ropes.

Name: plastic nets and pieces of net 2.5 cm  ≥ ≤  50 cm
Definition: Pieces of plastic open-meshed material made of twine, cord, or something similar, used typically for catching fish; smaller than 50 cm in the longest dimension.

Name: plastic nets and pieces of net > 50cm
Definition: Pieces of plastic open-meshed material made of twine, cord, or something similar, used typically for catching fish; bigger than 50 cm in the longest dimension.

Name: plastic tangled nets/cord
Definition: Tangled nets/cord made of plastic.

Name: single-use plastic gloves
Definition: Single-use plastic gloves used for example in relation to the COVID-19 pandemic.

Name: plastic headwear
Definition: Plastic headwear.

Name: fish boxes - hard plastic
Definition: Boxes made of plastic materials (other than expanded polystyrene), which are used for packaging fish or other seafood.

Name: plastic construction related waste
Definition: Plastic construction waste.

Name: fish boxes - foamed polystyrene
Definition: Boxes made of foamed polystyrene, which are used for packaging fish or other seafood.

Name: plastic food consumption related items
Definition: Plastic food consumption related items.

Name: plastic fishing line
Definition: A long nylon thread, usually attached to a baited hook, with a sinker or float, and used for catching fish. The fishing line may be found tangled or not and with or without hooks, sinkers and floats.

Name: plastic drink bottles
Definition: Plastic drink bottles.

Name: plastic fishing light sticks / fishing glow sticks incl. packaging
Definition: An item that is used by anglers in order to make baits more attractive to fish. Fishing light sticks or glow sticks are typically tubes filled with fluorescent fluid. They can be found in a variety of sizes.

Name: other plastic fisheries related items not covered by other categories
Definition: Other fisheries related litter items that are not explicitly addressed by the fisheries related items included on this list e.g., soft and hard plastic baits such as wobblers, spinners, etc.

Name: plastic food containers made of foamed polystyrene
Definition: Foamed polystyrene containers used for carrying or storing food, such as fast food containers, lunchboxes, etc.

Name: plastic floats for fishing nets
Definition: An item attached to the top of some types of fishing nets, like seine and trammel that keeps them hanging vertically in the water. Floats come in different sizes and shapes.

Name: plastic food containers made of hard non-foamed plastic
Definition: Plastic containers used for carrying or storing food, such as fast-food containers, Tupperware, lunchboxes, etc. Made of non-foamed plastic.

Name: plastic tableware/cups/cutlery/plates/trays/straws/stirrers
Definition: Plastic tableware cups/cutlery/plates/trays/straws/stirrers.

Name: plastic floats/buoys other source than fishing or not known
Definition: Plastic floats/buoys other source than fishing or not known. floating devices that serve as navigation marks, marking reefs or other hazards, mooring locations. They can be anchored (stationary) or allowed to drift with ocean currents.

Name: cups and cup lids of foamed polystyrene
Definition: Single-use cups and their lids for coffee and other drinks; made of foamed polystyrene. They have a wide range of uses in restaurants, bakeries, or catering settings.

Name: cups and lids of hard plastic
Definition: Single-use cups and their lids for coffee and other drinks; made of non-foamed artificial polymer materials. They have a wide range of uses in restaurants, bakeries, or catering settings.

Name: plastic fenders
Definition: Plastic cushions (such as foam rubber) placed between a boat and a dock or between two boats to lessen shock and prevent chafing.

Name: plastic cutlery
Definition: Single-use knives, forks, and spoons.

Name: plastic plates and trays
Definition: Single-use plates and trays made of artificial polymer material.

Name: plastic buckets
Definition: A roughly cylindrical open container with a handle made of plastic and used to hold and carry liquids

Name: plastic stirrers
Definition: Stirrers are used when serving hot drinks such as tea and coffee or other drinks such as cocktails.

Name: plastic straws
Definition: A drinking straw or drinking tube is a small pipe that allows its user to more conveniently consume a drink.

Name: plastic food packets and wrappers
Definition: Plastic food packets and wrappers.

Name: plastic crisps packets/sweets wrappers/lolly & lollypop sticks
Definition: Plastic crisps packets/sweets wrappers/lolly & lollypop sticks.

Name: plastic strapping bands
Definition: Plastic bands and straps used for fastening any type of package. Polypropylene and polyester strapping is the most commonly used plastic strapping on the market. Usually made of quite hard plastic.

Name: plastic sheets, industrial packaging, sheeting
Definition: Large plastic packaging or sheeting used for the protection or covering/wrapping of large cargo objects. Plastic sheeting is used for a variety of industrial and commercial applications. It comes in many sizes, strengths, styles, and colours depending on the application.

Name: plastic fisheries related items
Definition: Plastic fisheries related items.

Name: fibre glass items
Definition: Items made of fibreglass, a common type of fibre-reinforced plastic using glass fibre. Examples of fibreglass items include water pipes, pods, domes, traffic lights, pieces of boats etc.

Name: plastic fish boxes
Definition: Fish boxes for packaging fish or other seafood.

Name: plastic hard hats/helmets
Definition: A hard or padded protective hat, various types of which are worn by construction workers, workers from offshore installations, soldiers, police officers, motorcyclists, sports players, and others.

Name: plastic shotgun cartridges
Definition: A shotgun cartridge is a self-contained cartridge often loaded with multiple metallic "shot", which are small, generally spherical projectiles. The shells consist of a plastic tube mounted on a brass base holding a primer. Also plastic wads from shotgun cartridges can be found on their own.

Name: footwear made of plastic materials
Definition: Shoes/sandals/flipflops made of plastic materials.

Name: plastic traffic cones
Definition: Plastic cone-shaped objects that are used to separate off or close sections of a road.

Name: foamed plastic items and fragments not made of foamed polystyrene
Definition: Foamed plastic items and fragments not made of foamed polystyrene.

Name: packaging and/or insulation of foamed plastic
Definition: Lightweight cellular foam (mainly foamed PU and PE materials) used especially for insulation (i.e., in walls, roofs, and foundations as thermal insulation and water barrier) or as a packing material.

Name: fragments of foamed and non-foamed plastic material 2.5cm  ≥ ≤  50cm
Definition: Plastic/foamed polystyrene pieces 2.5 cm  ≥ ≤  50 cm.

Name: fragments of foamed and non-foamed plastic material > 50 cm
Definition: Plastic/foamed polystyrene pieces > 50 cm.

Name: fragments of non-foamed plastic 2.5cm  ≥ ≤  50cm
Definition: Fragments of plastic that are bigger than 2.5 cm and smaller than 50 cm in the longest dimension and originate from unidentifiable plastic non-foamed polystyrene items.

Name: plastic string and filaments exclusively from dolly ropes
Definition: Strings and filaments from blue, black or orange string that are used to protect bottom trawling nets against wear and tear. A dolly rope consists of around 30 strings; each string has around 25 threads.

Name: other plastic string and filaments exclusively from fishery
Definition: Other string and filaments exclusively from fishery.

Name: fragments of non-foamed plastic > 50cm
Definition: Fragments of plastic that are larger than 50 cm in the longest dimension and originate from unidentifiable plastic non-foamed polystyrene items.

Name: plastic tangled nets and rope without dolly rope or mixed with dolly rope
Definition: Tangled pieces of plastic open-meshed material made of twine, cord, or something similar, used typically for catching fish. They may be found tangled with rope or dolly rope.

Name: plastic tangled dolly rope
Definition: Tangles of a blue, black or orange rope that are used to protect bottom trawling nets against wear and tear. A dolly rope consists of around 30 strings; each string has around 25 threads. The dolly rope string as well as the separated threads can occur in tangles in the marine environment. Tangles of dolly rope should consist entirely of dolly rope.

Name: fragments of foamed polystyrene 2.5 cm  ≥ ≤  50 cm
Definition: Fragments of foamed polystyrene that are bigger than 2.5 cm and smaller than 50 cm in the longest dimension and originate from unidentifiable polystyrene items.

Name: plastic crab/lobster/octopus traps & pots and their tops
Definition: Stationary traps or pots used to catch crustaceans such as lobsters, crabs and octopus. Though the size and shape of the traps may vary, most feature a net covering and a cone-shaped entrance tunnel through which a crab or lobster is enticed with bait. Pots typically having a volume of 4 litres. Octopus seeking refuge in the pots can be trapped.

Name: fragments of foamed polystyrene > 50cm
Definition: Fragments of foamed polystyrene that are bigger than 50 cm in the longest dimension and originate from unidentifiable polystyrene items.

Name: plastic CDs & DVDs
Definition: Small plastic discs (and their keep cases) on which sound and data can be stored (CDs & DVDs).

Name: plastic hunting related items
Definition: Plastic hunting related items.

Name: plastic commercial salt packaging
Definition: Heavy-duty sacks and other containers used for packaging and shipping salt.

Name: plastic personal hygiene and care related items
Definition: Plastic personal hygiene and care related items.

Name: plastic personal hygiene and care related bottles & containers
Definition: Plastic body care and cosmetics bottles & containers.

Name: plastic fin trees (from fins for scuba diving)
Definition: The plastic supports placed inside diving flippers or fins to keep them in shape.

Name: plastic masking/duct/packing tape
Definition: Different sorts of plastic adhesive tape: used in painting, to cover areas on which paint is not wanted (masking tape); strong cloth-backed waterproof adhesive tape (duct tape); box-sealing tape, parcel tape or packing tape used for closing or sealing corrugated fibreboard boxes.

Name: telephone
Definition: Mobile phone devices and any other type of telephones.

Name: plastic construction waste
Definition: Plastic waste materials generated during the construction, renovation, and demolition of buildings or structures. These may include drainage pipes, waste pipes, plastic tubes for cables, construction foam, etc. Not foamed insulation materials.

Name: plastic flower pots
Definition: A plastic container in which plants are grown.

Name: other plastic personal hygiene and care items
Definition: Other identifiable personal hygiene and care items that do not fit in any other category of this list. Can be made of other materials than artificial polymers.

Name: plastic sanitary towels/panty liners/backing strips, tampons and tampon applicators
Definition: Absorbent pads worn by women to absorb menstrual blood. Sanitary towels/panty liners/backing strips, tampons and tampon applicators.

Name: plastic biomass holder from sewage treatment plants and aquaculture
Definition: Plastic Filter Media or Biofiltration Media are small (1-4 cm diameter ca. 1 cm high) usually round plastic items that look a bit like a cake. https://www.bing.com/images/search?q=Plastic+Filter+Media+or+Biofiltration+Media&FORM=HDRSC2

Name: plastic bait containers/packaging
Definition: Plastic packaging (pouches, bags) and plastic containers suitable for storing, transporting, selling fishing baits.

Name: plastic cable ties
Definition: A cable tie (also known as a wire tie, hose tie, steggel tie, zap strap or zip tie, and by the brand names Ty-Rap and Panduit strap) is a type of fastener, for holding items together, primarily electrical cables or wires.

Name: plastic wet wipes
Definition: A small disposable synthetic cloth treated with a cleansing agent, used especially for personal hygiene.

Name: plastic medical related items
Definition: Plastic medical related items.

Name: plastic single-use face-mask
Definition: Single-use facemask used to protect against for example dust, chemicals and pathogens (e.g., COVID-19 pandemic).

Name: plastic cotton bud sticks
Definition: A short plastic stick with a small amount of cotton on each end that is used for cleaning, especially the ears. The cotton is usually no-longer attached. The ends are rough when touched, where the cotton was attached. This feature can be used to separate from lolly sticks.

Name: plastic sanitary towels/panty liners/backing strips
Definition: Sanitary towels/panty liners/backing strips.

Name: plastic toilet fresheners
Definition: Toilet bowl fresheners, which are attached inside the toilet bowl to keep it smelling fresh.

Name: plastic undefined use
Definition: Plastic undefined use.

Name: plastic diapers/nappies
Definition: Basic garments for infants consisting of absorbent synthetic polymer material drawn up between the legs and fastened about the waist, used to retain urine and faeces.

Name: plastic syringes/needles
Definition: A plastic tube with a nozzle and piston or bulb for sucking in and ejecting liquid in a thin stream, used for cleaning wounds or body cavities, or fitted with a hollow needle for injecting or withdrawing fluids. Includeds all parts of syringes found separately.

Name: plastic engine oil bottles & containers
Definition: Plastic engine oil bottles & containers

Name: plastic medical/ pharmaceuticals containers/tubes/ packaging
Definition: A wide variety of artificial polymer packages used for the packaging of the wide variety of pharmaceutical solids, liquids, and gasses. Some of the common primary plastic packages are: blister packs, small bottles and containers, tubes, ampoules, etc.

Name: plastic dog/pet faeces bag
Definition: A plastic bag used for picking up and removing the faeces of a dog or other pet.

Name: plastic flip-flops
Definition: A light sandal made of plastic, with a thong between the big and second toe.

Name: other hard plastic or foamed polystyrene items (identifiable)
Definition: Other plastic/foamed polystyrene items (identifiable).

Name: rubber balloons
Definition: A small, coloured, rubber sack-like object which is inflated with air and then sealed at the neck, used as a child’s toy or a decoration. Within this category any balloon ribbons, strings, plastic valves and balloon sticks that are or were attached to balloons.

Name: rubber balls
Definition: A spherical toy ball, usually fairly small, made of elastic material which allows it to bounce against hard surfaces.

Name: rubber boots
Definition: A tall boot that is made of rubber and that keeps the feet and lower legs dry.

Name: rubber tyres & belts
Definition: A rubber covering, typically inflated or surrounding an inflated inner tube, placed round a wheel to form a soft contact with the road (tyre); a continuous rubber band of material used in machinery for transferring motion from one wheel to another (belt).

Name: rubber inner-tubes & rubber sheet
Definition: Rubber inner-tubes & rubber sheet.

Name: wheels with metal hub
Definition: A circular object that revolves on an axle and is fixed below a vehicle or other object to enable it to move easily over the ground. Includes the hub with the tyre or just the hub.

Name: rubber band (small, for kitchen/household/post use)
Definition: A thin, flexible loop that is made of rubber and used to hold things together.

Name: rubber condoms (incl. packaging)
Definition: A thin rubber sheath, used during sexual intercourse as a contraceptive or as a protection against infection. Within this category also the packaging should be recorded.

Name: other rubber pieces
Definition: Other identifiable rubber pieces, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: plastic heavy-duty sacks
Definition: Heavy duty sacks are plastic sacks typically designed to contain more than 25 kg of content such as animal feed, fertilizers, garden rubbish, etc.

Name: cloth textile clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves
Definition: Cloth textile clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves.

Name: plastic clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves
Definition: Plastic clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves.

Name: plastic mesh bags for vegetable, fruit and other products
Definition: A special mesh bag made out of polypropylene, polyethylene or high-density polyethylene used for packaging and transporting agricultural products such as vegetables, fruit, bird feed, etc.

Name: footwear made of plastic - not flip flops
Definition: Items of footwear made of plastic - not flip flops.

Name: clothing
Definition: Any type of clothes, garments and headwear made of natural or artificial polymer materials.

Name: shoes & sandals made of leather and/or textile
Definition: Various types of footwear such as shoes and sandals made of leather and/or textile.

Name: cloth textile backpacks & textile bags
Definition: Textile receptacles with an opening at the top, shoulder straps or a handle, used for carrying things.

Name: hessian sacks/packaging
Definition: Sacks and other packaging items made of a strong, coarse fabric from hemp or jute (Hessian).

Name: cloth textile carpet & furnishing
Definition: Thick woven fabric used for covering the floor or other fabric used for furniture, fittings, and other decorative house accessories such as curtains.

Name: sails, canvas
Definition: A heavy durable cloth made of cotton, hemp, or jute, used for sails, tents, etc.

Name: plastic tampons and tampon applicators
Definition: A feminine hygiene product designed to absorb the menstrual flow or a plug of material used to stop a wound or block an opening in the body and absorb blood or secretions. The tampon applicator should be recorded within this category.

Name: other textiles
Definition: Other textile items, including pieces of cloth, rags, etc. that are unidentifiable, as well as other identifiable cloth textile items, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: paper bags
Definition: A small bag made of paper, commonly used as shopping bags, packaging, etc.

Name: cardboard boxes
Definition: A thick, stiff paper that is used to make boxes and models.

Name: paper cartons/Tetrapak milk
Definition: Containers made of carton with a plastic-lining used for milk.

Name: other foamed plastic items and fragments not made of foamed polystyrene
Definition: Items and fragments (other than packaging or insulation related) made out of foamed sponge-like plastic, such as mattresses, bathing sponges, etc.

Name: paper cartons/Tetrapak (non-milk)
Definition: Containers made of carton with a plastic-lining used for food products, other than milk.

Name: fragments of foamed and non-foamed plastic material
Definition: Hard and foamed fragments of plastic material.

Name: fragments of foamed polystyrene
Definition: Fragments of foamed polystyrene.

Name: paper cigarette packets
Definition: A rectangular container made of paperboard, used as packaging for cigarettes. It may also include a plastic covering.

Name: paper cups, food trays, food wrappers, drink containers
Definition: Paper cups, food trays, food wrappers, drink containers.

Name: paper newspapers & magazines
Definition: Printed publications consisting of paper sheets and containing news, articles, advertisements.

Name: fragments of non-foamed plastic
Definition: Fragments of plastic that originate from unidentifiable plastic non-foamed polystyrene items.

Name: paper tubes and other pieces of fireworks
Definition: Small paper/cardboard containers/tubes filled with explosive chemicals that produce bright coloured light patterns or loud noises when they explode (fireworks).

Name: paper fragments
Definition: Fragments of paper items that cannot be identified.

Name: other paper items
Definition: Other identifiable paper and cardboard items, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: wooden corks
Definition: A bottle stopper made of cork or a similar material. Note that plastic corks should be recorded under plastic caps and lids

Name: other identifiable foamed plastic items
Definition: Items that are made of foamed polystyrene, which are identifiable but do not fit in any other litter type category in this list.

Name: other identifiable non-foamed plastic items
Definition: Items that are made of non-foamed artificial polymers, which are identifiable but do not fit in any other litter type category in this list.

Name: wooden pallets
Definition: A flat wooden structure on which heavy goods are put so that they can be moved using a fork-lift truck.

Name: wooden crates, boxes, baskets for packaging
Definition: Wooden containers typically used to transport or store different types of items and products. Not fish boxes.

Name: plastic rope, string, cord
Definition: Rope, string, cord made of plastic.

Name: wooden crab/lobster pots
Definition: Stationary wooden traps used to catch crustaceans such as lobsters and crabs. Usually covered in a net.

Name: wooden fish boxes
Definition: Boxes made of wood, which are used for storing or transferring fish or other seafood.

Name: plastic string and cord (diameter less than 1cm) not from dolly ropes or unidentified
Definition: A material consisting of threads made of plastic twisted together to form a thin length, with a diameter smaller than 1 cm; excluding string and cord from dolly ropes.

Name: wooden ice-cream sticks, chip forks, chopsticks, toothpicks
Definition: Various wooden sticks, including sticks from ice-creams, small wooden forks from fast food suppliers (chip forks), tapered sticks of wood held together in one hand and used as eating utensils in Asian cuisine (chopsticks), short pointed pieces of wood used for removing bits of food lodged between the teeth (toothpicks).

Name: plastic paint brushes
Definition: A brush used for painting, typically consisting of bristles fastened into a wooden or plastic handle. Can be made of other materials than artificial polymers.

Name: wooden fireworks & matches
Definition: A small thin piece of wood or cardboard tipped with flammable chemicals that catch fire with friction (match); a small container filled with explosive chemicals that produce bright coloured patterns or loud noises when they explode (fireworks).

Name: other processed wooden items 2.5 cm ≥ ≤ 50 cm
Definition: Other identifiable processed wooden items smaller than 50 cm in the longest dimension, which do not fit in any other category of this list, e.g. planks, boards, beams.

Name: other processed wooden items > 50cm
Definition: Other identifiable processed wooden items larger than 50 cm in the longest dimension, which do not fit in any other category of this list, e.g., planks, boards, beams.

Name: other wooden items
Definition: Other wood.

Name: plastic recreation related
Definition: Plastic recreation related.

Name: metal aerosol/spray cans
Definition: A type of dispensing system which creates an aerosol mist of liquid particles; used with a can or bottle that contains a payload and propellant under pressure. Indicative examples of such items are: spray paints, cleaning spray foam, engine oil spray, etc.

Name: plastic remains of fireworks
Definition: The plastic remains of fireworks such as caps of rockets, covers for fuses, exploding parts of battery fireworks.

Name: metal drinks cans
Definition: Metal containers that are used for storing and selling e.g., beer, or soft drinks.

Name: plastic smoking related items
Definition: Plastic smoking related items.

Name: metal food cans
Definition: Metal containers that are used for storing and selling food such as beans, soup, fish, corn, etc.

Name: metal foil wrappers, aluminium foil
Definition: Thin aluminium sheeting or leaves used, especially, to cover and wrap food.

Name: metal bottle caps, lids & pull tabs from cans
Definition: Metallic caps and lids from bottles and containers, including the pull tabs from cans

Name: plastic vehicle related
Definition: Plastic vehicle related.

Name: metal disposable BBQs
Definition: A single-use barbecue grill made from a lightweight aluminium material.

Name: paper food consumption related items
Definition: Paper food consumption related items.

Name: paper containers for food and drink
Definition: Paper containers for food and drink.

Name: paper cartons/Tetrapak
Definition: Paper cartons/Tetrapak.

Name: metal appliances (refrigerators, washers, etc.)
Definition: Metal (mostly electrical) devices or pieces of equipment designed to perform a specific task such as air conditioners, dishwashers, clothes dryers, freezers, refrigerators, kitchen stoves, water heaters, washing machines, trash compactors, microwave oven, etc.

Name: metal tableware (e.g. plates, cups & cutlery)
Definition: Metal dishes or dishware used for serving food and dining, including cutlery, plates, cups, serving dishes and other useful items.

Name: metal fisheries related weights/sinkers, and lures
Definition: fisheries related items such as: weights/sinkers (a metal weight used in conjunction with a fishing lure or hook to increase its rate of sink, anchoring ability, and/or casting distance); lures (any bright artificial bait consisting of metal mounted with hooks and trimmed with feathers.

Name: paper cups
Definition: Cups for coffee and other drinks; made of cardboard. They have a wide range of uses in restaurants, bakeries, or catering settings.

Name: paper food trays, food wrappers, drink containers
Definition: Single-use food trays, food wrappers and drink containers, made of paper.

Name: paper personal hygiene and care
Definition: Paper personal hygiene and care.

Name: paper cotton bud sticks
Definition: A short paper stick with a small amount of cotton on each end that is used for cleaning, especially the ears.

Name: paper undefined use
Definition: Paper undefined use.

Name: other paper containers
Definition: Other paper containers.

Name: metal lobster/crab pots
Definition: A portable trap that traps lobsters or crayfish. It can be constructed of wire or metal and netting. An opening permits the lobster or crab to enter a tunnel of netting.

Name: metal industrial scrap
Definition: Metal resulting from the disuse of metal products such as parts of vehicles, building supplies, and surplus materials.

Name: metal drums & barrels
Definition: Large cylindrical metal containers used for storing or shipping bulk cargo, i.e. oil, chemicals, etc.

Name: other metal cans
Definition: Other metal containers that are used for storing and selling products that are not food or drinks or paints

Name: metal paint tins
Definition: Metal containers that are used for paint

Name: wire, wire mesh, barbed wire
Definition: A metal mesh woven, knitted, welded, expanded, photo-chemically etched or electroformed steel or other (wire mesh); a metal wire with or without clusters of short, sharp spikes set at short intervals along it, used to make fences.

Name: metal vehicle parts / batteries
Definition: Any part of a car or other transport vehicle (i.e., boat) made predominantly of metal, including vehicle batteries. Excluding wheels.

Name: rubber clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves
Definition: Rubber clothing, footwear, headwear, gloves.

Name: rubber footwear
Definition: Rubber footwear.

Name: metal cables
Definition: A thick metal wire or a group of wires usually inside a rubber or plastic covering, which is used to carry electricity or electronic signals.

Name: rubber personal hygiene and care
Definition: Rubber personal hygiene and care.

Name: metal household batteries
Definition: Small-sized batteries that are typically used in small electronic devices such as flashlights, cameras, etc.

Name: rubber undefined use
Definition: Rubber undefined use.

Name: other metal objects
Definition: Other metal objects.

Name: other metal pieces 2.5cm  ≥ ≤  50cm
Definition: Other identifiable metal items that are smaller than 50 cm in the longest dimension and do not fit in any other item category of this list.

Name: rubber sheet
Definition: Rubber sheeting made of rubber (or rubber-like artificial polymer). Rubber sheets are used for varied purposes e.g., flooring, under shower pans, drainage systems, as lining for water containers and in construction.

Name: other metal pieces > 50cm
Definition: Other identifiable metal items that are bigger than 50 cm in the longest dimension and do not fit in any other item category of this list.

Name: rubber belts
Definition: Rubber belts elongated rectangular rubber items.

Name: glass bottles
Definition: Glass or ceramic containers with a narrow neck, used for storing drinks or other liquids. Includes pieces of glass that can be identified as coming from a bottle.

Name: glass jars
Definition: Wide-mouthed cylindrical containers made of glass or pottery, especially used for storing food. Includes pieces of glass that can be identified as coming from a jar.

Name: rubber vehicle related items
Definition: Rubber vehicle related items.

Name: rubber inner-tubes
Definition: An inflatable usually ring-shaped rubber tube designed for use inside a pneumatic tire.

Name: glass light bulbs
Definition: A glass bulb inserted into a lamp or a socket in a ceiling, which provides light by passing an electric current through a filament or a pocket of inert gas. Includes all types, also halogen, LED, etc.

Name: rubber tyres
Definition: Rubber tyres from all types of vehicles.

Name: wooden food consumption related items
Definition: Wooden food consumption related items.

Name: wooden bottles-related items
Definition: Wooden bottles-related items

Name: glass and ceramic tableware (plates/cups/glasses)
Definition: Glass or ceramic dishes or dishware used for serving food and dining, plates, cups, glassware, serving dishes and other useful items for practical as well as decorative purposes.

Name: glass ceramic construction materials (bricks, tiles, cement)
Definition: Any glass and ceramic material which is used for construction purposes such as brick, roof tiles, floor tiles, bricks, cement, etc.

Name: wooden fisheries related items
Definition: Wooden fisheries related items.

Name: glass fluorescent light tube
Definition: A low-pressure mercury-vapour gas-discharge lamp that uses fluorescence to produce visible light.

Name: ceramic or glass octopus pots
Definition: Pots made of pottery, weighted with concrete, and typically having a volume of 4 litres. Octopus seeking refuge in the pots can be trapped.

Name: wood undefined use
Definition: Wood undefined use.

Name: pieces of glass/ceramic (glass or ceramic fragments ≥ 2.5 cm)
Definition: Fragments of pottery or glass items that cannot be identified (≥ 2.5 cm).

Name: other glass items
Definition: Other identifiable glass items, which do not fit in any other category of this list.

Name: other plastic medical items (swabs, bandaging, adhesive plasters etc.)
Definition: Items deemed necessary for the treatment of an illness or injury. These may include swabs, bandaging, adhesive plasters, etc. Can be made of other materials than artificial polymers.

Name: paraffin wax
Definition: All types of paraffin wax, refined or less refined. "Paraffin" and "wax" are often used as synonyms for paraffin wax! Paraﬃn wax is always a mixture of n-alkanes and, depending on the degree of purity, various secondary components, which can vary greatly.

Name: oil & tar
Definition: oil & tar

Name: wooden recreation related items
Definition: Wooden recreation related items.

Name: organic food waste
Definition: All types of non-packaged food and food remains.
